nodes.text: Winlion was one of the 1,000 moons of Iego, a group of moons that orbited the Outer Rim Territories planet Iego. Each of the moons was as mysterious as the planet itself, which was located at Standard Galactic Grid coordinates T-7. Its gray surface was dotted with numerous craters.

Winlion was mentioned in the 2017 reference book Star Wars: The Visual Encyclopedia. The art used for the moon in the Visual Encyclopedia originated in a piece of concept art title "Iego 1000 Moons" that was drawn by Jackson Sze on October 3, 2007 for Mystery of a Thousand Moons, an episode of Star Wars: The Clone Wars. The moon did not appear in the episode itself.
